{"mode":"human","topic":"How to manage and dealing with discussions about healthcare and COVID vaccines.","opinion":"Having spent years balancing the nuances of accounting where precision meets uncertainty, I find that discussing sensitive topics like healthcare and COVID vaccines calls for a blend of empathy and clear reasoning. As someone deeply engaged in both creative pursuits and structured thinking—thanks to my background in classical music and hiking, alongside being an immigrant adapting to Milan's unique culture—I approach these discussions with openness yet caution. I believe it is crucial to listen actively and validate others' concerns without immediately dismissing their views. For example, when encountering vaccine hesitancy or contrasting opinions on healthcare policies, I try to ask open-ended questions that allow the other person to share their perspective fully. This method not only creates a space for mutual respect but also helps me understand underlying fears or misinformation that may be driving resistance.

